Time Series Forecasting Model

UNIVARIATE MODELS
1.AutoRegressive Model(AR Model)
   - uses past values of TSD and predicts future
   - order of AR model denoted by 'p'
      AR(1), AR(2) i.e AR(p)
     p = no.of lagged(past) observations
     AR(p) yt = c + φyt-1 + φyt-2 + ...... φyt-p + et 
           (et=white noise,c=constant,φ=parameter of model,yt-1,yt-2=past values)
     AR(2) = c+φ1yt-1+φ2yt-2
     AR(1) = c+φ1yt-1

2.Moving Average(MA) Model
   - uses the past error terms (residual) and predicts future
   - order of MA model denoted by 'q'
       q = no.of lagged error terms
       yt = Et + θ1Et-1 +θ2Et-2 + ......+θqEt-q

3.AutoRegressive Moving Average Model(ARMA)
  - combines AR & MA model for forecating
  - captures both temporal dependencies & error terms
  - order(p,q)
   ARMA(p,q)
     yt = φyt-1 + φyt-2 + ...... φyt-p + θ1Et-1 +θ2Et-2 + ......+θqEt-q 

4.AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average Model(ARIMA)
  - integarting involves differentiating order
  - ARIMA (p,d,q)
    ARIMA(1,1,1)
    AR(1)
    differentiating order = 1st order
    MA(1)
    Δyt = φ1Δyt-1 + φ2Δyt-2 + ...... φpΔyt-p + Et + θ1Et-1 +θ2Et-2 + ......+θqEt-q

5.Seasonaility AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average Model(SARIMA)
    - SARIMA(p,d,q)(P,D,Q)m
               |       |    \_ period
      order of ARIMA   order of seasonal part  

